Transmission and capture data were analyzed in the
resolved resonance region using the multilevel
R-matrix code SAMMY. The chlorine data were fitted in
the energy range from 0.0253 eV to 500 keV, where
resonance parameters for 122 and 88 resonances for
35Cl and 37Cl were obtained, respectively. The
combination of the transmission and capture data led
to 12 new resonance assignments for 37Cl in the
energy range up to 150 keV. Above 220 keV 64 new
resonances for 35Cl were observed. In addition above
150 keV 64 new resonances to 37Cl were assigned.
A 6Li-loaded glass scintillation detector was
positioned in the beam at the 80-m flight station at
a distance of 79.827 m from the neutron source. The
measurements were made using different filters in the
beam under different experimental conditions.
The experiments were performed using
ORELA.
ORELA operated with a repetition rate of 525 Hz,
8-ns pulse width, and an average power of 7 KW.
Approved by author on May 21, 2015.
